records.addlTxt:
9:20 AM Defendant Timothy M Butts not in court. Andrew Mutchler in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Jessica Phelps in court for Timothy M Butts. 

Defendant fails to appear.
Atty Phelps has no information as to the whereabouts of her client.

State requests warrant for Defendant failing to appear for Court. 
ADA Mutchler would request a warrant with a $750 cash alternative.
Atty Phelps has no comment on the request for warrant by the state.  
Court questions the State for proper service. 
State informs the Court there was proper service. 
Court reviews the criminal complaint for probable cause. 
Court finds there is probable cause and grants the request for warrant.

BY THE COURT:
*  Warrant with $750 cash alternative
Notice of Assignment of Judge - Return to sender unable to forward
Initial appearance on July 18, 2022 at 01:45 pm.
No contact with the A.D.J. victim or victim's residence and a second address as stated on the record.

12:59 PM Defendant Timothy M Butts appeared by video, in custody. Prosecuting attorney Andrew Mutchler in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
BTC: Warrant is quashed
Defendant states he has an attorney that will be appearing.
Matter will be recalled later.
1:49 PM Court recalls case. Atty Phelps is not present.
Hearing scheduled for July 18, 2022 at 01:45 pm.

2:41 PM Prosecuting attorney Brian J Pfeil in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Timothy M Butts not in court.  Attorney Jessica Phelps in court for Timothy M Butts. 

Atty Phelps has no information to provide to the court at this time. 
Court questions if the summons and complaint were sent out. 
Atty Pfeil states the summons was sent on March 24, 2022.  

BY THE COURT:  Court finds complaint shows probable cause and authorizes a criminal warrant with a $250 cash alternative.
